chunks.content: Crystal Platform provides seamless integration with major cloud services, enabling you to build powerful applications with managed infrastructure.
Crystal Platform works with all major cloud providers:

Compute Services - EC2, Lambda, ECS integrationStorage - S3, EBS, EFS supportDatabases - RDS, DynamoDB, DocumentDBNetworking - VPC, CloudFront, Route 53 Acme Platform automatically optimizes your AWS resource usage to minimize costs.

Get Acme Platform up and running in your project in just a few minutes.
Before installing Acme CLI, make sure you have: [Unknown component: CheckList]

Install Acme CLI globally or as a dev dependency: # Global installation
npm install -g acme-cli

# Or as a dev dependency
npm install --save-dev acme-cli
Run Acme CLI without installing: npx acme-cli init
To verify your installation is working correctly: acme --version You should see the version number displayed.

Start the development server to preview your application: acme dev Your application will be available at http://localhost:3000. Make sure port 3000 is available, or specify a different port using --port flag.
Now that Acme CLI is installed, you can: Learn about the Quick Start processExplore Core FeaturesCustomize your Configuration

Welcome to Acme Platform, the comprehensive solution that empowers modern teams to build, deploy, and scale applications with ease. Acme Platform provides everything you need to go from idea to production in minutes, not days.

Acme Platform is an innovative cloud-native platform that combines the power of modern infrastructure with developer-friendly tools. It helps teams: Rapidly deploy applications to the cloudScale automatically based on demandMonitor performance in real-timeCollaborate effectively across teams
[Unknown component: CheckList]
Explore our guides to get started quickly:

Acme Platform follows a simple three-step process: Connect Your Code - Link your Git repository to Acme PlatformAutomated Build - Our system automatically builds and tests your applicationDeploy & Scale - Your app is deployed with automatic scaling and monitoring Acme Platform supports all major programming languages and frameworks, including JavaScript, Python, Java, Go, and more.

Ready to transform your development workflow? Here's what you need to get started: A Git repository (GitHub, GitLab, or Bitbucket)A cloud account (AWS, Azure, or GCP)5 minutes of your time Let's move on to the Installation Guide to set up your first Acme Platform project. Make sure to secure your API keys and credentials before deploying to production.
Acme Platform is designed to work with teams of all sizes, from solo developers to enterprise organizations. Never commit sensitive information like passwords or API keys to your repository.
[Unknown component: CheckList] [Unknown component: CheckList]
Get your first Crystal Platform application running in under 5 minutes.

Initialize a new Crystal Platform project: mkdir my-app && cd my-app
crystal init You can also initialize Crystal Platform in an existing project directory.

Your crystal.config.json should look like this: {
  "name": "My Crystal App",
  "description": "A sample application built with Crystal Platform",
  "environment": "development",
  "region": "us-east-1",
  "runtime": "nodejs20"
}
Deploy to the cloud: crystal deploy [Unknown component: CheckList]
Your application will be available at a generated URL: crystal status The deployment usually takes 2-3 minutes. You'll receive a URL once it's ready.
